message: He never held any Guinness World Records. Marilyn vos Savant was the person with the highest IQ by Guinness World Records.
He is not a mathematician

I cannot believe this guy lied so many things here. His mother was not a teacher at the Seoul National University. There's absoutely no evidence that he actually attended the University of Colorado at age 8. He is also not an alumini of Grant High School (Los Angeles) and Hanyang University. He didn't complete the 12 years of mandatory education in 2 years. In fact, he barely passed the college entrance exam at 19. A good case of Ripley Syndrome.

He never attended the NASA. There is simply no proof other than his own statement. NASA does not accept a foreign national 8-year-old kid. There's no such record. Aslo, the dederal child labor law generally prohibits the employment of minors. If anyone seriously believe that he worked at NASA at age 8, I must say you are dumb. His father also confessed that it was a lie to attract public attention. What's worse, Kim failed at mathematics and English when he took a college entrance exam in Korea.
Says who? Who decides the act of boosterism? High schooler like you? Go play somewhere else.

It seems like McGill's average entering grade is no longer the highest in the country according to the most recent Maclean's data (2021 Fall). However, you shouldn't have deleted the whole paragraphs related to reputation and ranking labelling them as "advertisements". See Wiki pages of other US and Canadian universities.

It does not violate WP:BOOSTER and WP:UNDUE; see wiki pages of University of California, Berkeley and University of Toronto; If you want to commit an act of vandalism, then go to other univ pages and do the same.

You mentioned that Maclean's actually makes sure none of its publications uses the phrase "best university", but now you are slightly revising your statements. It does use phrases like "best" comprehensive or "best" undergraduate university. The edited version does not even contain the word "best" anyways. You have yet to provide a reason why I have to participate your revision to satisfy your ego. There's no official rule that "medical-doctoral" has to be included in the description.
You are not even reading the source. I gave you the url. It does use terms such as "no.1" or "best" to describe an university (not particularly McGill) and your statements are wrong.
No, actully Macleans does use the "best university" phrase. It used phrases such as "no.1 university" or "best comprehensive university" in the past. https://education.macleans.ca/rankings/
It's essentially the same thing. Even Macleans used the word "best" and "no.1". https://education.macleans.ca/university-rankings/mcgill-is-canadas-no-1-medical-doctoral-university-rankings-2023/
